-# Reusable MAAP (reverse acronym) explainer for page help and other guidance.
%h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 What is MAAP?
%p.mb-2
  MAAP is a reverse acronym. In OG, clarity work is organized around four building blocks, explained here from
  %strong Position
  through
  %strong Milestones:
%dl.mb-0
  %dt.fw-semibold.mb-1 Position
  %dd.mb-2
    OG companies strive for fairness. Positions hold the title and the expected Assignments, and they are the key to fair pay—every position has a salary attached to it.
  %dt.fw-semibold.mb-1 Assignment
  %dd.mb-2
    The actual job, broken into easy-to-understand sets of outcomes that are more actionable to coach.
  %dt.fw-semibold.mb-1 Abilities
  %dd.mb-2
    The skills, knowledge, behaviors, and overall competencies needed to fulfill Assignments.
  %dt.fw-semibold.mb-1 Milestones
  %dd.mb-0
    The standard five tiers of Abilities: wielding with a little help (M1); trusted to wield with no help (M2); expert who mentors others (M3); setting the standard for what expert means (M4); recognized in the industry for wielding the Ability (M5).
